commit_message:
Fixes heat exceptions

When calling heatclient and an exception is raised, the current code
doesn't return the error and instead returns an exception noting
heatclient has failed.  This patch includes the message from the
exception raised by the heatclient during a call to validate a stack.

Change-Id: I84abc7543da2510efca90973a7447e5cd1a0d3ad

commit_message:
Move to oslo_db

Replace the sqlalchemy engine and session management with an oslo.db
facade. This does the work transparently and fixes connection
mismanagement.

The changes involve:
- modifying the sqlalchemy session script to use oslo_db functions
- adding the oslo_db engine configuration parameters
- tweaking the faked tests to pass*

* the faked tests are sensitive to sleep calls and oslo_db uses a
  sleep(0) hack which was causing issues. The coverage of the tests was
  not affected.

Implements: blueprint move-to-oslo-db
Change-Id: I59f1fc0fe1551b9a815a51e6a620fabf060b013f

subject: Fix DeprecationWarning when call method delta_seconds
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2015-12-16 05:44:34.000000000', 'files': ['oslo_utils/timeutils.py'], 'message': "Fix DeprecationWarning when call method delta_seconds

We deprecated method total_seconds in 3.1, but method delta_seconds
still use it, this leads DeprecationWarnings in Nova which uses
method timeutils.delta_seconds. So don't call total_seconds in method
delta_seconds.

Change-Id: Iad3aca09f2b0c7abce8046931c4ecbc59a09e4c0
"}]
commit_message:
Fix DeprecationWarning when call method delta_seconds

We deprecated method total_seconds in 3.1, but method delta_seconds
still use it, this leads DeprecationWarnings in Nova which uses
method timeutils.delta_seconds. So don't call total_seconds in method
delta_seconds.

Change-Id: Iad3aca09f2b0c7abce8046931c4ecbc59a09e4c0

commit_message:
Remove warning for option type not a ConfigType

The documentation for cfg.Opt[1] only says that the type parameter
must be a callable object, not that it must be a subclass of
types.ConfigType, so there shouldn't be a warning from the config
generator when the type is not a subclass of types.ConfigType.

[1] http://docs.openstack.org/developer/oslo.config/opts.html#oslo_config.cfg.Opt

Change-Id: Ia38b471d52b3987b65d93b11d805c523276bdbfc
Closes-Bug: 1525275

commit_message:
live-mig: Mark migration as failed on fail to schedule

In case we reach maximum retires to schedule - we want to mark the
migration record as failed, since the whole operation will be aborted at
that point.

Change-Id: I3528e98b2dc596995556aec83bb65104b671571d
Partial-bug: #1417667

commit_message:
Move the Migration set-status-if-exists pattern to a method

We already use this pattern in places where we need to keep backwards
compatibility with an older RPC client that may not be sending the
migration object over.

Instead of it being a repetitive check, we make it a static
method on the ComputeManager class, and document that it can be removed
with the next major compute RPC version bump, in a single place instead
of a random comment.

Change-Id: I46632322f7abf3e329ebaab6587c7421d69bb861

commit_message:
Remove onSharedStorage from evacuate API

The patch I4217bd00d8c253db522241885dba2847a26af6df made the
on_shared_storge flag optional in the compute api in Liberty.
This patch removes the corresponding onSharedStorage flag from the
REST API as nova can easily detect this information.

APIImpact
DocImpact

Implements: bp remove-shared-storage-flag-in-evacuate-api
Change-Id: I54bfa1275e188573c1b95d770d89160a86cdf52c

commit_message:
Increase informations in nova-net warnings

The warning about the IP leased that is not associated only includes
the conflicting address, not any other useful information like the mac
address. Instead of just using the address include the whole fixed_ip
object.

This will help us get to the bottom of bug #1526737

Change-Id: I77487c9e5563dc84df0fb8120e7aba7bea9cdcc2

commit_message:
Replace safe_utils.getcallargs with inspect.getcallargs

safe_utils.getcallargs was written to support python2.6 which did not
have inspect.getcallargs.  Now that support for python2.6 has been
dropped it should be replaced with inspect.getcallargs.

Change-Id: Idf5b9a7f4d10b81b1be9aed26505e3acaa6f7e24

This commit removes a check for a valid accounts.yaml file before

commit_message:
Remove pre-check for test accounts file in credential factory

This commit removes a check for a valid accounts.yaml file before
we use the preprov cred provider. This masks real configuration issues
and makes it very confusing for users to see when something doesn't
work because it defaults to trying to use the legacy provider. Since
we'll actually fail to load a missing accounts.yaml file now this also
adds a check for IOError and raises an InvalidConfiguration exception
with a descriptive message instead.

Change-Id: I9c02b406746af799f8939e0b9d06c14b48302a7e

revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2015-07-02 15:20:22.000000000', 'files': ['nova/cells/filters/flavor_classes.py', 'nova/tests/unit/cells/test_flavor_classes_filter.py'], 'message': 'Flavor Classes: Add cells scheduler filter.

This filter is best explained by the doc string in the module:

"""
Flavor classes are defined by setting the 'class' key on a flavor's
extra_specs (instance_type['extra_specs']['class']).

Cells can announce that they only support certain flavor classes by setting
the 'capabilities' nova.conf option under the [cells] config section.  The
value of this option should be 'flavor_classes=name1;name2;name3' to
advertise that they support flavor classes 'name1', 'name2', and 'name3'.

Imagine this configuration:

flavor #1 extra_specs['class'] = 'highio'
flavor #2 extra_specs['class'] = 'standard'

Cell #1 nova.conf:

------- 8< -------
[cells]
enable=true
name=cell1
capabilities=flavor_classes=highio;some_other_class,some_other_cap=abc
------- 8< -------

Cell #2 nova.conf:

------- 8< -------
[cells]
enable=true
name=cell2
capabilities=flavor_classes=standard;some_other_class,some_other_cap=abc
------- 8< -------

Note the capabilities syntax:
 * '=' to match each key=val pair in a single capability
 * ','  to separate capabilities
 * ';' to separate the list of capability values

With this filter, building flavor #1 will go to cell1.  Flavor #2 will go
to cell2.
"""

Change-Id: I88646cfbf1fbfb442f9dd36112ecb5f6f87b8f4c
'}]
commit_message:
Flavor Classes: Add cells scheduler filter.

This filter is best explained by the doc string in the module:

"""
Flavor classes are defined by setting the 'class' key on a flavor's
extra_specs (instance_type['extra_specs']['class']).

Cells can announce that they only support certain flavor classes by setting
the 'capabilities' nova.conf option under the [cells] config section.  The
value of this option should be 'flavor_classes=name1;name2;name3' to
advertise that they support flavor classes 'name1', 'name2', and 'name3'.

Imagine this configuration:

flavor #1 extra_specs['class'] = 'highio'
flavor #2 extra_specs['class'] = 'standard'

Cell #1 nova.conf:

------- 8< -------
[cells]
enable=true
name=cell1
capabilities=flavor_classes=highio;some_other_class,some_other_cap=abc
------- 8< -------

Cell #2 nova.conf:

------- 8< -------
[cells]
enable=true
name=cell2
capabilities=flavor_classes=standard;some_other_class,some_other_cap=abc
------- 8< -------

Note the capabilities syntax:
 * '=' to match each key=val pair in a single capability
 * ','  to separate capabilities
 * ';' to separate the list of capability values

With this filter, building flavor #1 will go to cell1.  Flavor #2 will go
to cell2.
"""

Change-Id: I88646cfbf1fbfb442f9dd36112ecb5f6f87b8f4c

[{'number': 7, 'created': '2015-07-11 14:34:33.000000000', 'files': ['nova/virt/ironic/driver.py', 'nova/cells/manager.py', 'nova/tests/unit/virt/ironic/test_driver.py', 'nova/tests/unit/cells/test_cells_manager.py', 'nova/cells/messaging.py', 'nova/tests/unit/cells/test_cells_messaging.py', 'nova/cells/rpcapi.py'], 'message': 'Ironic: block storage support

This adds support for block storage in the Ironic driver. This method is
meant for in-band use; i.e. hardware that does not allow volumes to be
attached via some out-of-band method. This is currently limited to iSCSI
volumes.

This puts the volume connection info in the instance metadata, where the
user should retrieve it and manually mount the volume. The user will

commit_message:
Ironic: block storage support

This adds support for block storage in the Ironic driver. This method is
meant for in-band use; i.e. hardware that does not allow volumes to be
attached via some out-of-band method. This is currently limited to iSCSI
volumes.

This puts the volume connection info in the instance metadata, where the
user should retrieve it and manually mount the volume. The user will
also need to manually unmount the volume to avoid potential data
corruption when the server is powered off.

This also adds a cells RPC call for updating instance metadata in the
top cell, so that the user can fetch the iSCSI connection info from the
API.

Change-Id: Iaec76f642eec53dfd6745cf6cd3b6b2de5596c92

commit_message:
Allow long-running ramdisks for agent driver

This checks if power is already on when deploying, and does not
reboot the node if so. This relies on the assumption that any
node with power on that may be deployed to, is running the agent
ramdisk.

commit_message:
Don't bind ironic networks immediately

This adds the ability for Nova to send the bind_requested flag with
Neutron port-create calls, and the ability for the virt driver to choose
whether or not this is sent as True or False. This defaults to True,
which is the default today.

Ironic needs to do late-binding of ports, as it will need to update the
port object with more information necessary for doing the actual
binding, such as switchport etc. It also doesn't want to give the
machine access to the tenant networks during provisioning, and so won't
bind the port until provisioning is complete.

See also the ironic spec on the subject:
https://review.openstack.org/#/c/187829

Change-Id: I46c318963cc9cf050aa84db140588f20dbead98a

commit_message:
Add support of hbase database

We have done wrapper and lib for installing nosql databases
(hbase for now) they can be executed via enable_serivce hbase
in localrc.

HBase and Cassandra are supported as database backends in
Ceilometer, MagnetoDB projects, and it can be useful for
development and gating to have it in devstack.

We have implemented Cassandra as part of MagnetoDB devstack integration (
https://github.com/stackforge/magnetodb/tree/master/contrib/devstack) and
started working on HBase now

Here are several blueprints on this occasion
- MagnetoDB
  https://blueprints.launchpad.net/magnetodb/+spec/database-plugin-hbase
  https://blueprints.launchpad.net/magnetodb/+spec/devstack-add-hbase
- Ceilometer
  https://blueprints.launchpad.net/ceilometer/+spec/hbase-tests-on-real-backend

Implements: blueprint add-hbase-to-devstack
Co-Authored-By: Aleksey Chuprin <aleksei_chuprin@symantec.com>
Change-Id: I03fe2ce665b8b21371ee171c1b9f760534c3f2a9

When the Neutron Controller processes a "create" request, it
will check that the tenant_id is valid and add it to the
resource dict. Hence, the _get_tenant_id_for_create() can be removed,
as proposed in Neutron.

commit_message:
Add transaction for setting agent_id in L3HARouterAgentPortBinding

To avoid having extra L3HARouterAgentPortBinding with l3_agent as
None, operation of setting l3_agent should be atomic.
For this purpose, transaction was added in methods
create_ha_port_and_bind and _bind_ha_router_to_agents.

Closes-Bug: #1499647

Conflicts:
	neutron/scheduler/l3_agent_scheduler.py

Change-Id: Iaad82fe522cfd70061daecf411c924fdc11b7e41
(cherry picked from commit 3fef15a40b2714c1a372216ce60cc1384dc48c02)

commit_message:
Avoid duplicating tenant check when creating resources

When the Neutron Controller processes a "create" request, it
will check that the tenant_id is valid and add it to the
resource dict. Hence, the _get_tenant_id_for_create() can be removed,
as proposed in Neutron.

Change-Id: Icea06dc81344e1120bdf986a97a6b1094bbb765e
Partial-Bug: 1513825

commit_message:
Change node name from CLI (fuel1)

Added possibility to change node name:
`fuel node --node-id --name NewName`
The functionality for fuel2 has been already merged
in separate patch.

Also unit tests added.

Partial-Bug: #1498523

commit_message:
Add check that list of agents is not empty in _get_enabled_agents

No reason to try get enabled_agents and send notification
if there are no any agents associated with network.

commit_message:
Rename command to audit

This patchset is there to change the code structure.

Some Python class and packages need to be renamed
for a better compliance with the shared terminology
which provides a better understanding of Watcher
objects and components by every contributor.

This patchset is there to rename the folder command to audit

Partially implements: blueprint glossary-related-refactoring

Change-Id: I76616fb58d5e79a7dc209b80e882d216850d18a4

commit_message:
Fixes issue with loading default settings.yaml

fuelmenu fails to start with its default /etc/fuel/astute.yaml.
For now if some indexes failed to load just a warning message will be printed.

Change-Id: I83c0f90c66944c225ce7642df3a3a2e7b9b83371
Closes-Bug: #1513719
Signed-off-by: Ruslan Aliev <raliev@mirantis.com>

commit_message:
only get details when required

when POSTing measures to a metric, we don't need to know the full
resource details. only when we GET the metric of a resource does
the api need to know the resource details. this should making POST
requests a bit more efficient.

Change-Id: Ic26c2dec6a0d3697c05978f0a32786946b7407bb

commit_message:
Replace oslo_utils.timeutils.isotime

This change introduces ec2api.openstack.common.timeutils that
substitutes the deprecating functions from oslo_utils. Using the
isoformat in the datetime lib will change the time format in API.
So it is better to carry this function in ec2-api. The deprecation
happens in this commit.
https://review.openstack.org/#/c/252898/

Change-Id: Id3606e7ca73ab3e7d58cfe6131984dbf0f3b7e4d

During nova-specs/nova reviews, it is difficult to check all API changes
for following api-wg guideline because there is a lot of nova-specs/nova
patches. There are some common mistakes against following guideline,
then this patch adds a part of the guideline to the code-review guideline
for avoiding these mistakes.

Change-Id: I2192e9ffd3026057dc01006bd0ba419140c5b5b0
'}]
commit_message:
Add reviewing point related to REST API

During nova-specs/nova reviews, it is difficult to check all API changes
for following api-wg guideline because there is a lot of nova-specs/nova
patches. There are some common mistakes against following guideline,
then this patch adds a part of the guideline to the code-review guideline
for avoiding these mistakes.

Change-Id: I2192e9ffd3026057dc01006bd0ba419140c5b5b0

if the ping command remains stuck waiting for a response for more
than 5 minutes.

commit_message:
Pass environment variables of proxy to tox

When a development environment is under a proxy, tox is failed even if
environment variables of the proxy are set.

This patch fixes this problem.
Closes-Bug: #1525115

commit_message:
Replacement argparse by click

Argparse is not flexible like click. We are going to extend command
line interface for fuel-devops with command groups and nested sub
commands. To avoid complexity solution we will use click lib
instead of argparse.

blueprint: replacement-argparse-by-click

commit_message:
Replacement argparse by click

Argparse is not flexible like click. We are going to extend command
line interface for fuel-devops with command groups and nested sub
commands. To avoid complexity solution we will use click lib
instead of argparse.

revisions:

When using just 2 last segments of the path to table for generating
accessor method name it's possible that resulting names will clash,
say for Project->Compute->Volumes->Volumes and for
Admin->System->Volumes->Volumes. To avoid this situation, we need to

Closes-Bug: #1467615
"}]
commit_message:
Fix 3-components accessors for TabbedTables in i9n tests

When using just 2 last segments of the path to table for generating
accessor method name it's possible that resulting names will clash,
say for Project->Compute->Volumes->Volumes and for
Admin->System->Volumes->Volumes. To avoid this situation, we need to
use 3 components name for tables which are at 4th level of nesting.

Change-Id: If63ae14a99f4c53030927f96a69b7189bd83c4e5
Closes-Bug: #1467615

subject: Set Nova's ram_allocation_ratio configuration option to "1.0" By default
revisions:
[{'number': 1, 'created': '2015-12-10 11:51:26.000000000', 'files': ['elements/puppet-stack-config/puppet-stack-config.pp'], 'message': 'Set Nova's ram_allocation_ratio configuration option to "1.0" By default

the Nova's "ram_allocation_ratio" is "1.5", this doesn't make sense for
baremetal because we can't allocate more memory than the machine already
has.

By leaving it as default ("1.5") will cause scheduling instances to
fail in case the amount of RAM in the node's is exactly the same amount
requested in the flavor.

Closes-Bug: #1524752
Change-Id: I4e6cc3457c62ad1a0f3b81247e1718e492973e8c
'}]
commit_message:
Set Nova's ram_allocation_ratio configuration option to "1.0" By default

the Nova's "ram_allocation_ratio" is "1.5", this doesn't make sense for
baremetal because we can't allocate more memory than the machine already
has.

By leaving it as default ("1.5") will cause scheduling instances to
fail in case the amount of RAM in the node's is exactly the same amount
requested in the flavor.

Closes-Bug: #1524752
Change-Id: I4e6cc3457c62ad1a0f3b81247e1718e492973e8c

commit_message:
change osd_pool_size to 3

Minimum Ceph object replication factor suitable for production is 3. We
historically set the default to 2 for testing purposes with a
recommendation to increase it to 3 in production deployments, but Fuel
usage statistics shows that most users ignore the recommendation and
leave the default.

Change-Id: Ie1a2d866eef8c3f988b8bb240079b931ddcdb03a
Closes-Bug: #1523864

commit_message:
Add python-memcached to list of installed pkgs on controllers

We use memcached for a few services but can't rely on the python
module being installed as a dependency because it techincally isn't
needed unless one configures the services to use memcached.

More at: https://bugzilla.redhat.com/show_bug.cgi?id=1271433#c12

Change-Id: I462532ca49157b57b4a558922bd3cb2cbce103e6
(cherry picked from commit 655f4ea7027b7f2bcda3d3479db4b644415d936b)

subject: Log all resource events during overcloud deploy
revisions:
[{'number': 2, 'created': '2015-12-14 02:35:33.000000000', 'files': ['tripleoclient/tests/test_utils.py', 'tripleoclient/tests/v1/overcloud_deploy/test_overcloud_deploy.py', 'tripleoclient/utils.py', 'tripleoclient/v1/overcloud_deploy.py'], 'message': 'Log all resource events during overcloud deploy

This change switches the overcloud deploy stack polling with event
list polling. This uses the same technique as the recently added
heat stack-create --poll mode: Ib7d35b66521f0ccca8544fd18fb70e04eaf98e5a

There is a (CREATE|UPDATE)_(COMPLETE|FAILED) event generated when the stack
operation is complete, so this is used to decide when to stop polling.

Also, every time there is an event it is printed to the screen in log
style. This would give the user an indication that something is
happening, which is better than staring at nothing for minutes (hours).

On stack update, the oldest event from the previous operation is discovered and
that is used for the marker so that only new events are logged.

Change-Id: I8951b0b924db769961aa67e654fcbd774d3e7787
(cherry picked from commit a6ff771ab773e5214f46c1a86d8d829d74903e16)
'}]
commit_message:
Log all resource events during overcloud deploy

This change switches the overcloud deploy stack polling with event
list polling. This uses the same technique as the recently added
heat stack-create --poll mode: Ib7d35b66521f0ccca8544fd18fb70e04eaf98e5a

There is a (CREATE|UPDATE)_(COMPLETE|FAILED) event generated when the stack
operation is complete, so this is used to decide when to stop polling.

Also, every time there is an event it is printed to the screen in log
style. This would give the user an indication that something is
happening, which is better than staring at nothing for minutes (hours).

On stack update, the oldest event from the previous operation is discovered and
that is used for the marker so that only new events are logged.

Change-Id: I8951b0b924db769961aa67e654fcbd774d3e7787
(cherry picked from commit a6ff771ab773e5214f46c1a86d8d829d74903e16)

commit_message:
We do not need to pass a NeutronControlPlaneID

The Neutron port poperty accepts either an ID or a Name, we can
default to 'ctlplane' in the template, don't need to pass an ID
from the client.

Change-Id: I3a1a0f4ac198b29b694062c8106d691aba1208b3
Related-Bug: 1526014

Enable simple json format in workflow signal

simple json format, using a new resource
property: "use_request_body_as_input".

Client should request/report share size in GiB instead

commit_message:
Fix share size units to match the API

Similar issue has been handled in CinderClient in
bug/1511167.
The API docs list the size units as gibibytes(GiBs).
Client should request/report share size in GiB instead
of gigabyes(GB). Hence made the corrections.

Change-Id: I25465e68a713613646e2350a443660fc4b3850a2
Closes-bug: 1516841

commit_message:
Removes MANIFEST.in as it is not needed explicitely by PBR

This patch removes `MANIFEST.in` file as pbr generates a sensible
manifest from git files and some standard files and it removes
the need for an explicit `MANIFEST.in` file.

Change-Id: I3da83a8f86cc6cef274f151d053d7b645e4d6894

commit_message:
Neutron port, tolerate switching network name/id

It's valid to switch the network name for an ID referencing the
same network, and vice-versa so allow that behavior when using the
network property which can accept either name or ID.

This has been squashed with I289a88c1a9c3351df976424504bc14a5ec878573
to make backporting easier:

Neutron port allow switching between network_id and network

The network_id property is deprecated, so we should tolerate switching
to the not-deprecated network property without replacing the port.

Conflicts:
	heat/engine/resources/openstack/neutron/port.py

Also modified heat/tests/neutron/test_neutron_port.py to make tests pass.

(cherry picked from commit 3a82e0cd59f8d4bb9308969109dead0d7887c2f3)
(combined with review I289a88c1a9c3351df976424504bc14a5ec878573)

Partial-Bug: #1514680
Change-Id: I0889ff8fc277dc9703d30b7e42fd799cfb57e975
